In a series of authored films, some of our most engaging experts reveal their favourite hidden objects, forgotten places and artistic passions
 

1/11 John Bly investigates the Kimbolton Cabinet, an exquisite piece of English furniture

2/11 An exploration of Viking culture and its long-lasting influence on the British Isles.

3/11 Lucy Worsley tells the story of Bolsover Castle in Derbyshire.

4/11 Stuart Kelly explores Abbotsford House including its newly discovered secret corners.

5/11 Clemency Burton-Hill explores the life and influence of violin maker Antonio Stradivari.
